  "text": "In [CITATION_1] , Washington et. al extended the algorithm presented in [CITATION_2] to the case where the link between adjacent nodes consisted of multiple wavelengths, each with a number of sub-rate streams. Bifurcation of traffic was permitted, meaning that on each link a call may use sub-rate traffic streams that belong to different wavelengths. As a result, the total number of available sub-rate streams is assumed to be very large. Two slightly different approximations were used for the analysis of each subsystem were modifications of the Nilsson et. al recursion. When the number of servers per node was small, one of the proposed algorithms had better accuracy than the link independence algorithm. However, as the total number of servers increased, the link independence algorithm exhibited better accuracy as well as faster execution times. In this work, we extend the work of [CITATION_3] to provide a better approximation of each loss node in the analysis over proposed subsystems.",
